<%- include("partials/head", { title }) %>
<%- include("partials/navbar") %>

<main class="page wide">
    <section class="panel">
        <p class="eyebrow">Project details</p>
        <h1>Node.js API app with CI/CD validation.</h1>
        <p class="hero-text">
            This project is a small Pokédex application built to practice API consumption,
            automated testing, linting, and GitHub Actions CI.
        </p>

        <div class="about-grid">
            <article>
                <h2>Application</h2>
                <p>Node.js and Express serve the frontend and expose backend API routes.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h2>External API</h2>
                <p>The backend calls PokéAPI, formats the response, and returns only useful data.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h2>Testing</h2>
                <p>Jest and Supertest validate the API routes. External API calls are mocked.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h2>Quality</h2>
                <p>ESLint checks JavaScript quality before code is merged or shipped.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h2>CI</h2>
                <p>GitHub Actions installs dependencies, runs lint, and runs tests on every push.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h2>Next step</h2>
                <p>Add artifact generation and later a deployment target.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>

</body>
</html>